got it — here’s a clean, cache-free, thread-safe utility you can drop in:
	•	You pass an existing BlobContainerClient (so it plugs into your code).
	•	It builds the blob name from inputs, applies your fallback order, reads the blob, and maps to a POJO.
	•	If the blob content is JSON, it maps to TemplateDocument (subject/bodyHtml/bodyText/metadata).
If it’s plain text, it still returns a TemplateDocument with bodyText filled.

